---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Software guides for small teams: reviews, roundups, and comparisons"
description: "Independent, dated guides for solo founders and 5–50 person teams. We spell out pricing cliffs, admin work, and renewal traps that marketing pages skip."
---

<div class="home">
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
    <div class="hero__shell motion-reveal motion-reveal--1">
      <div class="hero__grid">
        <div class="hero__content">
          <p class="hero__eyebrow">
            <span class="hero__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            Independent · written for small teams
          </p>
          <h1 id="hero-title" class="hero__title">Buy software with the fine print in view.</h1>
          <p class="hero__lede">
            Reviews, roundups, and side-by-side comparisons in plain language. We focus on what is easy to miss until you are paying the bill: seat
            limits, admin time, renewal jumps, and the "starter tier" walls.
          </p>
          <ul class="hero__chips" aria-label="What we cover">
            <li>Pricing at scale</li>
            <li>Admin and setup load</li>
            <li>Renewals and SKUs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <aside class="hero__panel" aria-label="About this site">
          <p class="hero__panel-kicker">What you are reading</p>
          <div class="hero__stat" role="group" aria-label="Published guides count">
            <span class="hero__stat-value">{{ collections.posts | length }}</span>
            <span class="hero__stat-label">guides in the library</span>
          </div>
          <p class="hero__panel-copy">
            Each piece is dated. We link out to vendors when it helps you verify pricing and limits; where we earn a commission, we say so up front.
          </p>
          <ul class="hero__trust">
            <li class="hero__trust-item">
              <span class="hero__trust-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path
                    d="M9 1.75 15.25 4.5v4.25c0 3.45-2.55 6.65-6.25 8.5C5.3 15.4 2.75 12.2 2.75 8.75V4.5L9 1.75z"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="1.35"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                  />
                  <path d="M6.25 9 8.1 10.85 12.1 6.9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.35" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span><strong class="hero__trust-strong">Audience:</strong> solo founders and 5–50 person teams (global English).</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hero__trust-item">
              <span class="hero__trust-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path
                    d="M3.5 5.25h11M3.5 9h11M3.5 12.75h7.5"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="1.35"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                  />
                  <rect x="2.25" y="2.75" width="13.5" height="12.5" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.35" />
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span><strong class="hero__trust-strong">Format:</strong> long-form guides, not scraped specs or one-line blurbs.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="hero__trust-item">
              <span class="hero__trust-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <circle cx="9" cy="9" r="6.75" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.35" />
                  <path d="M9 5.65V9l2.35 1.55" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.35" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span>
                <strong class="hero__trust-strong">Money:</strong>
                <a class="hero__panel-link" href="{{ '/affiliate-disclosure/' | url }}">Affiliate disclosure</a> (how links are used).
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="hero__panel-accent" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="feed" aria-labelledby="feed-title">
    <div class="feed__head motion-reveal motion-reveal--3">
      <h2 id="feed-title" class="feed__title">Latest guides</h2>
      <p class="feed__subtitle">Reviews, roundups, comparisons, and short notes, sorted by publish date so you can see what is new.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="post-list">
      {% for post in collections.posts %}
        <li class="post-card post-card--{{ post.data.type }} motion-reveal motion-reveal--stagger">
          <div class="post-card__top">
            <span class="type-pill type-pill--{{ post.data.type }}">{{ post.data.type | contentTypeLabel }}</span>
            <time class="post-card__time" datetime="{{ post.date | htmlDate }}">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</time>
          </div>
          <h3 class="post-card__title">
            <a class="post-card__link" href="{{ post.url | url }}">
              <span class="post-card__link-text">{{ post.data.title }}</span>
              <span class="post-card__arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path
                    d="M4 9h10M10 5l4 4-4 4"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="1.6"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
            </a>
          </h3>
          {% if post.data.description %}
            <p class="post-card__dek">{{ post.data.description }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>
